<item>
            <title>[SEC-2897] ActiveDirectoryLdapAuthenticationProvider should use bindPrincipal not username</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/SEC-2897</link>
                <project id="10040" key="SEC">Spring Security</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Shouldn&apos;t the lines&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;return SpringSecurityLdapTemplate.searchForSingleEntryInternal(context, searchControls,&lt;br/&gt;
                   searchRoot, searchFilter, new Object[]&lt;/p&gt;
{username}
&lt;p&gt;);&lt;br/&gt;
actually be&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;return SpringSecurityLdapTemplate.searchForSingleEntryInternal(context, searchControls,&lt;br/&gt;
                   searchRoot, searchFilter, new Object[]&lt;/p&gt;
{bindPrincipal}
&lt;p&gt;);&lt;br/&gt;
?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This currently breaks our authentication.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
