                            <comment id="113276" author="tda" created="Mon, 9 Mar 2015 04:35:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I have been able to work around this issue by specifing the search filter as &lt;p/&gt;
&lt;div id=&quot;syntaxplugin&quot; class=&quot;syntaxplugin&quot; style=&quot;border: 1px dashed #bbb; border-radius: 5px !important; overflow: auto; max-height: 30em;&quot;&gt;
&lt;table cellspacing=&quot;0&quot; cellpadding=&quot;0&quot; border=&quot;0&quot; width=&quot;100%&quot; style=&quot;font-size: 1em; line-height: 1.4em !important; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; color: black;&quot;&gt;
		&lt;tbody &gt;
				&lt;tr id=&quot;syntaxplugin_code_and_gutter&quot;&gt;
						&lt;td  style=&quot; line-height: 1.4em !important; padding: 0em; vertical-align: top;&quot;&gt;
					&lt;pre style=&quot;font-size: 1em; margin: 0 10px;  margin-top: 10px;   margin-bottom: 10px;  width: auto; padding: 0;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: black; font-family: &apos;Consolas&apos;, &apos;Bitstream Vera Sans Mono&apos;, &apos;Courier New&apos;, Courier, monospace !important;&quot;&gt;(&amp;amp;(objectClass=user)(sAMAccountName={0}))&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;
			&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
			&lt;/tbody&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p/&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;As far as I understand the way Active Directory works is that &lt;em&gt;sAMAccountName&lt;/em&gt; is just the username while &lt;em&gt;userPrincipalName&lt;/em&gt; is in usually in the form &lt;em&gt;username@domain&lt;/em&gt;. The problem is that the default filter searches for just the username in &lt;em&gt;userPrincipalName&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="113355" author="rwinch" created="Tue, 10 Mar 2015 14:42:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for the report and workaround &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=tda&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;tda&quot;&gt;Daniele Torino&lt;/a&gt;!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is now fixed in 4.0.0.CI-SNAPSHOT and 3.2.7.CI-SNAPSHOT and is published in &lt;a href=&quot;https://repo.spring.io/libs-snapshot/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://repo.spring.io/libs-snapshot/&lt;/a&gt; Can anyone verify the issue is resolved?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="113360" author="tda" created="Wed, 11 Mar 2015 02:13:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=rwinch&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;rwinch&quot;&gt;Rob Winch&lt;/a&gt;. I just tested with &lt;em&gt;3.2.7.CI-SNAPSHOT&lt;/em&gt; and without workaround and it works perfectly.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="113374" author="rwinch" created="Wed, 11 Mar 2015 09:00:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=tda&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;tda&quot;&gt;Daniele Torino&lt;/a&gt; Thanks for the fast confirmation! I plan to have 4.0 and 3.2.7 out next week with the fix.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="125936" author="issuemaster" created="Sat, 6 Feb 2016 06:28:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This issue has been migrated to &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/spring-projects/spring-security/issues/3114&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://github.com/spring-projects/spring-security/issues/3114&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
